    {
      "instruction": "<p>Roll the<strong> lime<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span> </strong>with your hand on a hard surface (to release more juice) and cut into wedges</p><p>Add the <strong>peanut butter</strong> to a small bowl with the <strong>ginger & garlic paste</strong>, <strong>soy sauce</strong>,<strong> ground cumin</strong> and the juice of 1 <span class=\"text-danger\">[2] </span><strong>lime wedge<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> and mix until fully combined</p><p>Gradually whisk in 4 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[6 tbsp]</span><strong> boiled water</strong>, a little at a time, until a smooth, thick sauce remains – this is your <strong>peanut sauce</strong></p>",
