            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the fish is in the oven, trim the<strong> green beans</strong> and chop in half, then add the<strong> chopped beans </strong>to a large piece of <strong>tin foil</strong> with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp] </span><strong>cold water</strong>, a drizzle of<strong> olive oil</strong> and a pinch of<strong> pepper</strong></p><p>Scrunch the foil around the beans to form a tightly sealed parcel and add to a baking tray (Cooking for 4? Make 2 separate parcels!)</p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 10-12 min or until the beans are tender</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
